    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that sounds like you're just describing a hypothetical version of nationalism that doesn't really exist in practice. in the real world, looking at history, nationalism almost always leads to some kind of aggression or prejudice against outsiders. isn't it more accurate to say that nationalism is fundamentally an unstable and dangerous force in a globalized world?",
